DAMATURU – Members of the defunct APC Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee, today paid a farewell visit to the former Chairman of the Caretaker committee, Governor Mai Mala Buni. The members collectively commended Governor Buni for his excellent leadership style by carrying all members of board. They pointed out that the former chairman listened and gave everyone a sense of belonging. Members of the committee also commended Governor Buni for leading a peaceful and successful convention. Some of the members confessed that they have learnt so much from Buni’s commitment, determination and steadfastness in achieving set goals without giving attention to deliberate distractions. Responding, Governor Buni thanked members of the defunct committee for their sacrifices to the party. “Your support, cooperation and commitment to the party had immensely contributed to the success of the just concluded Convention. “I want to thank you very much and hope you will serve the party diligently with more commitment when next you are called upon to serve. POLL He reminded the former committee members to support the party in the 2023 General election “We should please support the party to succeed in the 2023 general election” Gov. Buni said.